{"word":"H1921 - הָדַר - hâdar - haw-dar' - Countenance","slug":"H1921","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">הָדַר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>hâdar"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>haw-dar'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Countenance"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D4;&#x05D3;&#x05E8; - ha&#x0302;dar</b> - <i>haw-dar'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>swell</i> up (literally or figuratively, actively or passively); by implication to <i>favor</i> or <i>honour</i>, <i>be high</i> or <i>proud: - </i>countenance, crooked place, glorious, honour, put forth."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1913\">H1913</a>, <a href=\"#/H1924\">H1924</a>, <a href=\"#/H1925\">H1925</a>, <a href=\"#/H1926\">H1926</a>, <a href=\"#/H1927\">H1927</a>"}]}